{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἁλμῠρ-ός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> (ἅλμη) <b>salt, briny,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus only in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”, and always in phrase ἁ. ὕδωρ\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>salt sea</b>-water, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.511\">Refs</a>], etc.; πόντος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 107, 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 26; θάλασσα 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica “Papyrus fragments” in E. Diehl, 25.10; καθ᾽ ἁ. ἅλα 5th c.BC: Epicharmus Comicus 53, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 76; βένθεα 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.57\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ποταμός, of the Hellespont, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.35. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in Prose, of taste, <b>salt,</b> γίνεται τὸ στόμα ἁ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Acut.(Sp.)” 44\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὄψα ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.2.31, compare 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης” 1.56; αἷμα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 84a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] assuming variant; of drinking-water, <b>brackish,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.26; ofsoil, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 6.10.1, LXX.Jer.17.6\">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to μῶρος (insipid), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Comica Adespota” 596. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>bitter, distasteful,</b> γειτόνημα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Alcman Lyricus 116, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 705a; ἀκοή “Phdr.” 243d; λόγοι 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 3.121e\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; ἁλμυρὰ κλαίειν weep <b>bitterly,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 23.34; ἁλμυρὸν καταπτύσαι 3rd c.BC: Cercidas Iambographus 19.37. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> <b>piquant,</b> ἁ. καὶ δριμύ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.685e.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6239","accentedUnicode":"ἁλμυρός","shortDef":"brackish","mediumDef":"brackish","stepGloss":"brackish","stepTransliteration":"halmuros","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}